So `fillOrder` would look like this:
```
function fillOrder(uint256 orderId) external whenNotPaused {
    // verify orderId is valid
    // verify order hasn't expired
    // if reduceOnly (or stop order), verify reducing is valid
    // verify target price is hit
    // remove order from openOrders list
    // execute the order (without external call):
    _executeLimitOrder(order);
    // send tip fee to keeper
}
```
Whereas it used to be:
```
function fillOrder(uint256 orderId) external whenNotPaused {
    // verify orderId is valid
    // verify order hasn't expired
    // if reduceOnly (or stop order), verify reducing is valid
    // verify target price is hit
    // remove order from openOrders list
    // execute the order (with external call):
    module.executeLimitOrder(order);
    // send tip fee to keeper
}
```
